div.span: must associate one of the builder objects with the director. Usually, its done just once, via parameters of the directors constructor. Then the director uses that builder object for all further construction. However, theres an alternative approach for when the client passes the builder object to the production method of the director. In this case, you can use a different builder each time you produce something with the director.
